16:30.432 --> 16:32.393
What?

16:32.434 --> 16:36.188
Hang on. I don't understand
what you're telling me.

16:36.230 --> 16:39.525
Okay, I'll come right over.

16:39.567 --> 16:41.569
What's wrong?

16:43.571 --> 16:45.573
Roman's in a coma.

16:48.617 --> 16:50.911
This is how you see yourself?

16:50.952 --> 16:53.038
This is how you
make me see myself.

16:53.080 --> 16:55.541
Thank you.

16:55.583 --> 16:58.711
- When did you learn those words?
- You were the only thing

16:58.753 --> 17:00.962
holding us together.
You always were.

17:01.004 --> 17:03.799
<i>I just wish I could
teach you how to see yourself.</i>

17:12.558 --> 17:15.685
What happened?

17:15.728 --> 17:17.688
A drug overdose.

17:17.730 --> 17:21.066
Can we talk downstairs?

17:25.613 --> 17:28.531
I haven't been in that
attic in 30 years.

17:28.574 --> 17:31.076
You know he should be
in a hospital.

17:31.118 --> 17:35.247
He's staying here.

17:35.289 --> 17:37.499
What drugs?

17:37.541 --> 17:39.710
A number, evidently.

17:39.752 --> 17:41.712
He was causing a scene
at the institute

17:41.754 --> 17:43.839
and Johann sedated him.

17:43.881 --> 17:47.551
Sedated him? That's
not sedation, Olivia.

17:47.593 --> 17:49.553
That's a coma.

17:49.595 --> 17:51.555
You left Pryce still breathing?

17:51.597 --> 17:53.557
The coma is Roman's,

17:53.599 --> 17:56.435
not Johann's. He did
what he had to do.

17:56.477 --> 17:58.729
- Why was he there?
- I don't know.

17:58.771 --> 18:00.731
I suppose Johann

18:00.773 --> 18:03.567
- doesn't either.
- Let it go, Norman.

18:03.609 --> 18:07.237
Do you know anything
about Project Ouroboros?

18:07.279 --> 18:11.533
I told you, I haven't got any better
idea what goes on there than you do.

18:11.575 --> 18:13.535
Then why was he there?

18:13.577 --> 18:16.538
Something's going on here.
You can't act like it's not.

18:22.127 --> 18:24.713
Liv.

18:26.715 --> 18:30.511
Liv, Liv, Liv.

18:42.982 --> 18:46.151
You know, you don't have
to do that anymore.

18:47.569 --> 18:49.822
Protect me from the truth.

18:49.864 --> 18:52.032
I know him.

18:54.034 --> 18:57.830
I'm sorry.

19:01.917 --> 19:04.169
Do you think
he's gonna wake up?

19:06.922 --> 19:09.466
Well,

19:09.508 --> 19:12.803
I think that's up to Roman now.

19:17.725 --> 19:20.268
The Godfrey boy's in a coma.

19:20.310 --> 19:23.188
I know. The heart aches.

19:24.899 --> 19:27.818
Nic.

19:27.860 --> 19:29.945
You old leg-humper.

19:29.987 --> 19:32.948
You know, there are better places
to have this conversation.

19:32.990 --> 19:35.617
We have time.

19:35.659 --> 19:37.619
We always have had time

19:37.661 --> 19:39.914
for each other.

19:42.207 --> 19:46.086
You also seem to have exhausted the
patience of the local law enforcement.

19:48.088 --> 19:50.716
Seems Roman Godfrey
had quite the night.

19:52.718 --> 19:55.136
It's the White Tower. There's
something happening there.

19:55.178 --> 19:57.514
Pryce is playing liar's poker.

19:57.556 --> 20:00.392
Francis Pullman saw his hand,

20:00.434 --> 20:04.563
drove a titanium syringe three
inches into his temporal lobe.

20:04.605 --> 20:08.233
- And Rumancek?
- They were at the mill.

20:08.275 --> 20:10.193
<i>They found the rest
of Willoughby.</i>

20:10.235 --> 20:12.112
<i>Or left her there.</i>

20:12.153 --> 20:14.698
<i>I'm not so sure.</i>

20:14.740 --> 20:18.368
No sooner did the Hardy Boys break up but
their mothers are seeing each other.

20:18.410 --> 20:21.204
Olivia Godfrey.

20:21.246 --> 20:23.916
She was at the mill too.

20:23.958 --> 20:26.043
Her name is on the place.

20:26.085 --> 20:29.463
<i>This was not
the first body to fall there.</i>

20:29.504 --> 20:31.465
<i>Prior to her taking
that name in 1993,</i>

20:31.506 --> 20:33.550
<i>there's no scrap
of history to be found.</i>

20:38.346 --> 20:40.682
But a woman like that...

20:42.810 --> 20:46.021
I suspect JR Godfrey's not the first
man to lose his head over her.

20:48.440 --> 20:50.859
I think she might be upir.

20:53.112 --> 20:56.657
- Why are we talking about Olivia Godfrey?
- Do I need to repeat myself?

20:56.698 --> 21:00.119
- I sent you here to hunt an animal.
- And I found a whole herd.

21:00.160 --> 21:04.123
Then what are we doing
in Peter Rumancek's trailer?

21:04.164 --> 21:07.208
I don't know.

21:07.250 --> 21:09.795
"I found myself in a dark wood,

21:09.837 --> 21:12.464
for the straight way was lost."

21:12.506 --> 21:14.466
If you're trying
to inform my direction,

21:14.508 --> 21:16.635
<i>I'd rather you didn't
quote the Inferno.</i>

21:16.677 --> 21:20.055
Dante had his Virgil
to guide him.

21:20.097 --> 21:22.432
Let me be yours.

21:22.474 --> 21:24.476
Forget Olivia Godfrey.

21:24.518 --> 21:26.269
Her footprint's
at the crime scene.

21:26.311 --> 21:28.480
- I confirmed it.
- She's a diversion.

21:28.522 --> 21:31.984
- She's a suspect. - You have great
instincts for the hunt, Clementine.

21:32.026 --> 21:34.569
Trust them.

21:36.822 --> 21:38.907
Clear your head

21:38.949 --> 21:41.952
and bring me Peter Rumancek.

22:33.795 --> 22:37.966
Thank you for coming back.

22:51.270 --> 22:53.356
I love you.

22:53.398 --> 22:56.944
I love you.

23:17.256 --> 23:19.716
Is this where the Dragon is?

23:19.758 --> 23:22.761
I don't know.
Ask yourself, Roman.

23:22.803 --> 23:25.722
You're the one with
the questions and the answers.

23:27.724 --> 23:30.185
Will you come with me?

23:30.227 --> 23:32.479
I can't.
You won't be alone.

23:32.520 --> 23:35.482
Everyone you blame for your mistakes is
waiting for you just on the other side.

23:35.523 --> 23:38.735
- I'm a warrior. Warrior!
- Prove it.

23:42.281 --> 23:44.532
All right.

24:01.382 --> 24:03.802
I'm here.
I can help you.

24:06.763 --> 24:09.766
Biologically speaking,
young girls have a blood rite

24:09.808 --> 24:13.145
that initiates them into adulthood,
whether they are ready for it or not.

24:13.187 --> 24:17.149
To compensate, all tribal cultures put
their young males through some ordeal

24:17.191 --> 24:20.777
at puberty, separating
the boy's world from the man's.

24:20.819 --> 24:23.530
It's not your fault
you're weak, Roman.

24:23.571 --> 24:27.117
- I'm not weak.
- You think Peter would cry over you?

24:41.256 --> 24:43.967
It's unusual for the knight
to take the king.

24:44.009 --> 24:45.969
The bishop

24:46.011 --> 24:48.680
has far greater talent
for the end game.

24:48.722 --> 24:51.933
Kneel.

24:59.524 --> 25:02.027
You think the Dragon

25:02.069 --> 25:04.821
gives a shit
about your nobility?

25:04.863 --> 25:08.116
He's gonna eat you alive.

25:08.158 --> 25:10.327
<i>He's gonna eat you alive.</i>

25:10.369 --> 25:14.248
He's gonna eat you alive!

25:30.555 --> 25:33.558
Have a seat.

25:40.815 --> 25:44.069
Roman, Roman, Roman.

25:44.111 --> 25:46.029
How can I help you?

25:46.071 --> 25:47.989
I'm looking for the Dragon.

25:48.031 --> 25:50.449
Well, let's see
what my Swiss colleague

25:50.491 --> 25:53.161
has to say about this.

25:53.203 --> 25:57.332
- Doctor. - The subject here
is in an unconscious condition,

25:57.374 --> 26:00.877
which he believes to be his catabasis, and
he won't be able to reach the surface

26:00.919 --> 26:05.548
if he doesn't "confront
the Dragon", Doctor.

26:05.590 --> 26:09.636
All consciousness
separates, but in dreams

26:09.677 --> 26:12.806
<i>we put on the likeness
of the more universal,</i>

26:12.847 --> 26:16.517
<i>truer, more eternal man</i>

26:16.559 --> 26:20.397
in the darkness
of primordial night.

26:20.439 --> 26:24.859
Oh, well, his sister's appearing to
him in the form of a guide, Doctor.

26:24.901 --> 26:27.070
To deliver a classic

26:27.112 --> 26:29.406
messiah archetype.

26:29.448 --> 26:32.617
<i>We know that our Shelley
lends herself to this, Doctor.</i>

26:32.659 --> 26:34.453
Then you believe
the purpose of this episode

26:34.493 --> 26:38.165
<i>- to be redemption, Doctor.
- It is recommended</i>

26:38.206 --> 26:40.834
that the subject
search for clues

26:40.875 --> 26:44.379
within the dream landscape.

26:44.421 --> 26:47.506
<i>In this instance,</i>

26:47.548 --> 26:49.801
the Dragon is clearly

26:49.843 --> 26:52.429
the subject's own shadow,

26:52.471 --> 26:55.807
the most repressed
of his inner thoughts.

26:55.849 --> 26:59.311
<i>As for the oft-mentioned</i>

